I grabbed the Chicken Tortilla Soup and the Beef Fajitas via delivery..  Both were excellent!  The soup came separated where the fresh ingredients were in there own container and the broth was in its own to prevent things from getting soggy and I really appreciated that. Once mixed together the soup was delicious.  The fajitas were great. But I was bummed they only provide 2 flour tortillas. IMO this dish should come with 4 as you could easily make 4 normal size fajitas with a couple strips of steak inside.  The sides for the fajitas came separate and were fresh. Rice tasted fantastic. The beans, IMO, weren't great flavor wise but overall okay to throw onto the fajita.  I'm definitely going to order take out from here again. Well worth a shot.  EDIT: Dined in and it was simply fantastic. The food is so damn authentic and taste wonderful. Cannot recommend this place enough!!!
The pork tacos are amazing, and the portions are generous. The staff is friendly. We had a great experience!
Really good

I stopped by with my husband for a sweet dinner date. The owner was super nice. He is clearly pouring his soul into this place. The food was incredible. The chips come with a lovely salsa AND super good bean dip. We ordered enchiladas and a chimichanga; both we incredible! We were allowed to try the homemade vanilla coconut flan with dulce de leche, too, which was incredible. We will definitely be going back because the menu has so much more we want to try. Everyone should support this business. But be warned, the food is cooked fresh, so you have to wait a bit for it. Regardless, service was excellent.

So delicious. We got the spinach chimichanga, and the chicken tortilla soup. Food was supremely packed for take out. Staff were so friendly and accommodating, even letting us try their (delicious) house made flan! Leaves other local Latin cuisine in the dust! This will absolutely be a go to place for us.

Went there to try their chimichanga, as I have sorely missed that dish. My first time eating one with spinach, but I am quite sure it won’t be my last. Flavor was excellent, as was the texture. I got mine to go and ate it shortly after that. As the dish is fried and served in sauce, I don’t suggest ordering a chimichanga to eat the next day.  They were out of paper menus to take with, so I’m hoping to have one to bring to my coworkers.

Amazing food comes out of this restaurant. Everything is made to order and with a lot of care. It is not an in and out burrito place so be prepared to for a normal restaurant wait, get an appetizer, that is well worth it. Take out is a great option as well. I like to eat in although there is tool for about 15-20 at most. The staff is super friendly.  Great vegetarian options as well. I love the spinach burrito and they grill each burrito at the end which is my favorite way.
I've had take out from here twice and it's all delicious! The homemade cheese is especially notable, but I don't think you'll find a bad thing on the menu.
Delicious little restaurant perfect for a quick bite or order out.
